Stock Market Simulation Requirements:

Stock Market – 
Contains random companies with their stock prices.
Stock Prices fluctuate up and down randomly
Sends out list of companies and price of stocks to client and bank periodically
Checks with bank to see if this client has sufficient funds to make purchase

Bank – 
Holds account balances of clients
Gets prices of companies’ stocks from stock market and awaits purchase from a buyer/client
Confirms to stock market that buyer has sufficient funds for a purchase

Client –
Looks up stock prices it gets from the stock market and decides what to purchase
Sends request to stock market of intent to purchase a stock.
Requests account balance from bank

Signer –
Verifies a purchase
